parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system failures can cause various safety issues, including loss of power, faulty brakes, and malfunctioning airbags, which can lead to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The symptoms include blown fuses
faulty turn signals
malfunctioning power outlets
and electrical fires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sliding door issues can cause safety risks, including doors opening while driving, which can lead to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The symptoms include faulty sliding door motors
doors not opening or closing properly

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake system failures can cause accidents and injuries due to loss of braking power.
symptoms: The symptoms include faulty brake switches
stuck brake pedals
and malfunctioning anti-lock braking systems (ABS).

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent no-start condition can cause inconvenience and safety risks, especially if the vehicle stalls while driving.
symptoms: The symptoms include faulty starters
ignition issues
and anti-theft system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fire hazards can cause serious safety risks, including injuries and fatalities.
symptoms: The symptoms include electrical fires
burning odors
and smoke coming from the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle position sensor can cause the vehicle to suddenly and unexpectedly lose power, leading to a loss of acceleration and potentially resulting in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly loses power
the check engine light illuminates
the vehicle decelerates rapidly
the accelerator pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle will not accelerate past a certain speed
and the vehicle may stall or idle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to suddenly and unexpectedly accelerate, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates without warning
the accelerator pedal feels stuck or unresponsive
the vehicle accelerates rapidly without driver input
and the brakes may not respond properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ESC system can cause the vehicle to lose traction and stability, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The ESC light illuminates
the vehicle loses traction or stability
the vehicle may skid or slide
and the brakes may not respond properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hood latch can cause the hood to fly open while driving, obstructing the driver's view and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The hood suddenly opens while driving
the hood does not stay closed
the windshield is damaged or broken.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sliding door latch can cause the doors to open or close unexpectedly, potentially trapping passengers or causing accidents.
symptoms: The sliding doors open or close unexpectedly
the doors do not open or close properly
the doors are stuck shut
the doors make a loud grinding noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inaccuracy of the speedometer can cause the driver to be unaware of their actual speed, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The speedometer does not accurately log miles and speed
